question: What are the names of the top 3 orders with a freight cost greater than 100?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Order)
WHERE toFloat(o.freight) > 100
RETURN o.shipName, toFloat(o.freight)
ORDER BY toFloat(o.freight) DESC
LIMIT 3
error: TypeQL does not support string-to-numeric conversion. The freight attribute is string type but the query requires numeric comparison (toFloat). Lexicographic string comparison would give incorrect results.

question: What are the names of the top 3 suppliers based on the average freight of orders they supplied?
cypher:
MATCH (s:Supplier)-[:SUPPLIES]->(p:Product)<-[:ORDERS]-(o:Order)
WITH s, o.freight AS freight
WHERE freight IS NOT NULL
WITH s, avg(toFloat(freight)) AS avgFreight
ORDER BY avgFreight DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN s.companyName AS supplierName, avgFreight
error: Schema has freight as string type; TypeQL has no toFloat() conversion function to enable mean() aggregation on string values

question: Which 3 products are most frequently ordered together?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Order)-[r:ORDERS]->(p:Product)
WITH o, collect(p.productID) AS products
UNWIND products AS product1
UNWIND products AS product2
WITH product1, product2, count(*) AS frequency
WHERE product1 < product2
RETURN product1, product2, frequency
ORDER BY frequency DESC
LIMIT 3
error: Unsupported: collect() and UNWIND for array operations - TypeQL has no array aggregation

question: Which 3 products have the most variations in unit price among orders?
cypher:
MATCH (p:Product)<-[:ORDERS]-(o:Order)
WITH p.productID AS productID, p.productName AS productName, o.unitPrice AS unitPrice
ORDER BY productID, unitPrice
WITH productID, productName, COLLECT(unitPrice) AS prices
WITH productID, productName, REDUCE(s = 0, i IN RANGE(1, SIZE(prices) - 1) | s + ABS(TOFLOAT(prices[i]) - TOFLOAT(prices[i-1]))) AS priceVariation
ORDER BY priceVariation DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN productName, priceVariation
error: Unsupported: COLLECT(), REDUCE with RANGE, SIZE(), and array indexing [i] for computing cumulative price variation
